# Maps & Address Logic

## File locations
- `convex/maps.ts` — Google Geocoding actions (`normalizeAndGeocodeAddress`, `computeDistanceAndZone`)
- `convex/addresses.ts` — address CRUD, `listDeliveryZones`, `upsertAddressCache`
- `convex/checkout.ts` — `getEligibility` reads `addressCache` + `deliveryTiers` for fee/eligibility
- `src/components/AddressAutocomplete.tsx` — Google Places Autocomplete (client-side)

## Caching
- `addressCache` table stores `distanceMiles`, `zoneId`, `eligibleDelivery`, `eligibleShipping` per address.
- `computeDistanceAndZone` action populates the cache; `getEligibility` query reads it.
- Cache is keyed by `addressId` — one entry per address.

## Rules
- Geocoding and distance computation are **actions** (external API calls). Never do these in queries or mutations.
- Address autocomplete uses `NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY` (client-side). Server geocoding uses `GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY`.
- When the API key is not configured, both degrade gracefully (autocomplete shows manual entry; server returns unvalidated address).
